From: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] test/mds: run unittest_mds_quiesce_db serially

Several QuiesceDbTest cases assert that a state transition is observed
within a tight wall-clock budget. ReleaseAwait wraps root1_state.wait()
in timed_run(sec(0.1), ...) and expects the agent callback to fire
within 100ms. That callback is driven by the quiesce db thread pushing
the next agent map, so the 100ms budget only holds when the db thread
(and the notified waiter) get scheduled promptly, which has implicitly
assumed an unloaded machine since the tests were introduced.

On a saturated -j63 ctest run the db thread or the waiter can be
preempted past the budget, timed_run times out and the assertion fails
although the state machine is correct (observed TestQuiesceDb.cc:1287
ReleaseAwait, Actual: false). A single such preemption is enough; the
window is ~101ms unloaded, so it sits right on the edge.

Mark the test RUN_SERIAL so ctest runs it alone, restoring the
premise. It takes ~10s, a negligible serial window for the suite. This
mirrors the fix for unittest_throttle.

Signed-off-by: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
---
 src/test/mds/CMakeLists.txt | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/test/mds/CMakeLists.txt b/src/test/mds/CMakeLists.txt
index 18ebb648e68..00000000000 100644
--- a/src/test/mds/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/test/mds/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -21,6 +21,7 @@ target_link_libraries(unittest_mds_sessionfilter mds osdc ceph-common global ${B
   $<TARGET_OBJECTS:unit-main>
 )
 add_ceph_unittest(unittest_mds_quiesce_db)
+set_property(TEST unittest_mds_quiesce_db PROPERTY RUN_SERIAL TRUE)
 target_link_libraries(unittest_mds_quiesce_db ceph-common global Boost::url)

 # unittest_mds_quiesce_agent
